  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "libjpeg-turbo security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libjpeg-turbo is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nThe PPM reader in libjpeg-turbo through 2.0.90 mishandles use of tjLoadImage for loading a 16-bit binary PPM file into a grayscale buffer and loading a 16-bit binary PGM file into an RGB buffer. This is related to a heap-based buffer overflow in the get_word_rgb_row function in rdppm.c.(CVE-2021-46822)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libjpeg-turbo is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "libjpeg-turbo",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
